Be kind to your inner child. Be kind to YOU. 

This year has been one of the hardest I’ve had in a long time. 
A year of massive change.
A year of loss & lots of tears.
Countless break downs, and almost giving up.
A year of chronic pain & health issues.
Seemingly, with no end in sight. 

It was also a year full of love.
Full of family & cherished memories.
A year of growth.
Of becoming a new me.
A year of setting stronger boundaries.
With many life lessons learned.
A year of friendships & laughter.
Of toddler giggles and kisses.
A year of RESILIENCE. 

So as we round the corner to 2023, I can’t help but reflect. 
10 years ago, I was a broken, wildly unhealthy girl filling a massive void with all the wrong things.
Where there once was shame, I now feel pride.
Where there was hurt, there is now healing.
Where there once was pain, there are now coping skills.

2022 has been my biggest reminder. 
Of where I came from. Of the problems I had then. Of the life I prayed for, that I now live. 
& all of a sudden, my perspective shifts into focus.
I have so many reasons to live.
I’m so glad I chose life & healing.
I’m so glad I chose recovery from those demons.
I thank my 20 year old self for not letting them swallow me whole. And for not giving up.

So while 2022 was challenging and painful, I’m thankful that I’m alive today. I’m thankful for my beautiful daughter & loving husband. For the roof over our heads, our careers that support us, and for our family and our health.

I am a beautifully crafted, chaotic masterpiece just trying to master PEACE 🕊️🤍 so thank you 2022 for reminding me how strong I really am. #beautifulmess

This one right here, this one made me cry happy tears 🥹 

It hasn’t been an easy road. It’s still not easy all the time. In fact, it’s still hard a lot of the time.

But to think of all I / we have overcome individually and as a family.

From challenging pasts to mental health issues, physical health diagnoses, infertility, family illness, postpartum recovery, new homes, new jobs, moving states, loss of loved ones, navigating motherhood while working, and marriage & parenthood.. I’m so dang proud.

Olivia has taught me more about life and about myself in the past 2 years than I ever thought possible. And everyday she shows me that my past doesn’t define my character as a mother.

This has always been a big one for me. I’ve always been terrified of how it would define me. But the only thing it has done is empower me and made me a better wife, mother, sister, daughter, friend & person.

My sweet girl, you’re my trailblazer. Truly my North Star - thank you for always being the reason WHY I keep pushing through, even on the days I’m just not sure how I’ll make it happen.

And to my mamas with colorful pasts & mental / physical health issues. I see you pushing through, doing what needs to be done, despite what your inner voice says or what others think. Despite the odds, the pain & the darkness. I see you finding the light. 

You’re the best mama 🤍 happy Friday my loves!

7 summers ago we packed our lives up and left Atlanta to move back to my home town, Asheville.

At the time we had only been dating a little over a year, not yet engaged with lots of uncertainty. I had just turned a 24 and Zach had just turned 28. We were babies with so much to figure out.

Flash forward 7 years. We’re back in the Atlanta area after 3 homes, a wedding, graduating college, a career change, starting a business, overcoming infertility, having a baby, health scares, navigating parenthood, a second across-state move, and many years of figuring life out together.

Hasn’t always been easy, hasn’t always been perfect, but it’s always been right with you by my side. I couldn’t love our little family more, and this beautiful life we’ve built together. Over 8 years together and so very proud of how far we’ve come 🤍

Late as usual, but I couldn’t let this go by without saying Happy Daughter’s Day to the brightest part of my life. 

Olivia, you light up every room with your bubbly personality. You’re so full of curiosity and wonder. No matter what we’re doing, you’re always filling us with laughter and joy. We may butt heads from time to time due to our strong-willed natures and determination once we’ve set our mind on something, but I know it will take you far in this life. I can handle the sass, I’m the one you get it from after all 💁🏼‍♀️😅 

Never stop being fierce, my girl. You continue to amaze me everyday and I couldn’t be more proud to be your mom.

I like you always, and love you forever 🫶🏼
Xx Mama

Thanks for the memories, 2023! 🥂🫶🏼 Another year full of ups and downs and amazing growth.

I always find New Year’s Eve to be bittersweet. As we say goodbye to the past, we reflect on where we started and where we’re at now. We think about how far we’ve come, yet all the things we still hope to accomplish. We are reminded that time is precious and will pass by if we don’t pay attention. It’s a time when we’re filled with anticipation of what the new year will bring. 

My two words for 2024? Stillness & peace. May this year bring many, many more memories with the people I love most 🤍✨ 

Anyone else get anxious on NYE or is that just me?! 🤔
